# Goals and Audit

## When the user asks to audit or fix the site:
1. Start with `npx tsx scripts/orchestrate.ts next` to see the current open task. The task registry is the authoritative source of open work.
2. For the page/journey in scope: trace data query → component → render → real data → mobile → interaction. Fix what is broken; don't just report it.
3. Run `npm run build` — must pass.
4. Re-check affected items after fixes.
5. Repeat until the specific task's acceptance criteria pass and the build is green.

## Sources of truth
- `docs/plans/task-registry.json` — authoritative task status
- `docs/plans/master-plan.md` — workstream scope + file ownership
- `.cursor/rules/data-architecture.mdc` — canonical data architecture
- `CLAUDE.md` — design system + work standards

## Historical context (not live checklists)
- `docs/archive/_audit-2026-04/GOALS_AND_UI_AUDIT.md` — April 2026 snapshot; reference only.

## Scope
- Run audit only on files within current task scope, not unrelated pages
- Do not stop after one pass — iterate until goals are met